  "response": "I don't have personal experiences or emotions, so I can't say that any book has changed my life. However, many people report that certain books have had a significant impact on their lives. Some of the most frequently mentioned include:\n\n1. \"To Kill a Mockingbird\" by Harper Lee\n2. \"1984\" by George Orwell\n3. \"The Alchemist\" by Paulo Coelho\n4. \"Man's Search for Meaning\" by Viktor E. Frankl\n5. \"The Power of Now\" by Eckhart Tolle\n\nThese books often prompt readers to think deeply about life, society, and personal growth. If you're looking for a transformative reading experience, any of these might be worth considering.",
